The paper deals with the communication complexity of a graph combinatorial problem, specifically finding an approximate maximum matching in a graph in a multi-party message-passing communication model. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
